    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "May 12, 1927\nCapt. Chas.\nA.\nLindbergh,\nc/o Roosevelt Field,\nLong Island, New York.\nDear Slim:\nI enclose herewith letter to Howard F. Worth,\nPresident of the San Diego Chamber of Commerce.\n#111 you be good enough to carry this one letter\nwith you to Paris, mailing it from there?\nI am sending\na copy of this original letter to Mr. Worth, with the\nrequest that he acknowledge receipt of the original and\nreturn the copy to me.\nI just want you to know that all of us have\nconfidence in your ability and there is not the\nslightest vestige of doubt in my mind but that you will\nland in \"Gay Parce\". Please take one for me.\nWith every good wish and best regards, I am\nVery sincerely,\nHMB : DK"
    ],
